cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "CoordPy: Bounded-context orchestration and evaluation SDK for AI agent teams"
message: "If you use CoordPy in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Context Zero Contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/adotdong29/context-zero"
url: "https://github.com/adotdong29/context-zero"
abstract: >
  CoordPy is the shipped product surface from the Context Zero
  research programme. It models cross-agent context as typed,
  content-addressed, lifecycle-bounded capsules with explicit
  budgets and provenance, and provides a reproducible RunSpec/
  RunReport contract plus a sealed capsule graph that downstream
  tools can audit and replay end-to-end.
keywords:
  - multi-agent
  - llm
  - bounded-context
  - provenance
  - auditability
  - evaluation
license: MIT
